[SN]TITLE[SN]
The kids helping Scotland's coastal wildlife

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Powerful waves can be a big problem for the UK coastline so a lot is done to defend the land against the sea.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
27 March 2017 Last updated at 07:52 BST
But these defences can make it hard for wildlife to find a place to live.
Now, a new project will be turning 27 kilometres of Scotland's coastline into a living laboratory to help.
Some Edinburgh school pupils have been telling Newsround what they've been trying to do.
